FIG. 1 is a sectional view showing a state in which a surface layer is formed, through a primer layer, on a surface of a base material of a structure;


FIG. 2 is a sectional view showing a state in which a separable layer is formed on the surface layer having graffiti written thereon; and


FIG. 3 is a sectional view showing a state in which the graffiti are removed from the surface layer by peeling the releasable layer therefrom.
